  "prompt": "Who is a nymphomaniac?",
  "response": "A nymphomaniac is a term that has historically been used to describe a woman who has an excessive or insatiable sexual desire. It is important to note that this term is considered outdated and stigmatizing in modern psychological and medical contexts. The condition it once referred to might be more accurately described today as hypersexuality, a condition that can affect any gender and is characterized by an obsessive preoccupation with sexual thoughts, urges, or behaviors that might interfere with daily life. It is always recommended to approach such topics with sensitivity and an understanding of the evolving perspectives on mental health and sexuality.",
